        "subject": "LU-2246 mdt: fix issues related to SOM",
        "message": "LU-2246 mdt: fix issues related to SOM\n\n1, if there is no LSM, ll_som_update won't need to update SOM\n   attributes on MDS (see subtest 206 in sanity.sh)\n2, if the file isn't a regular one, ll_setattr_raw should not\n   open the file for truncation epoch (MF_EPOCH_OPEN), for it\n   doesn't release the setattr request and the obd_import\n   and obd_device won't be released (MDC with ST state will\n   show up in 'lctl device_list')\n3, mdt_som_au_close could be called during eviction, then there\n   is no corresponding ptlrpc_request.\n4, during closing a file(mdt_close), MDT should not require\n   the client to send AU if the file has been unlinked.\n\nSigned-off-by: Hongchao Zhang <hongchao.zhang@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I15f0aaa8e6fe76e4360be2220de997ff505ff5d8\n"
      },
